title: jsuri: need to declare global Uri as type instead of var
body:
Declaring the global Uri as a var instead of as a type leads to runtime
errors as the jsuri script leaks Uri to global directly when not loaded
via AMD or CommonJS, instead of leaking a jsuri module object.

Developers working with jsuri in the global namespace need to use Uri
directly instead of prfacing with jsuri in order to avoid runtime issues
with 'jsuri' being undefined.

- Upgrade the fabricjs.d.ts typeings to the latest version of farbic.js (v1.5.0). The current typeings were long out of date, at least before version 1 of farbic.js. 
- Added in the JSDoc cooments from the fabric source. 
- This was more a total rewrite, so I append my name to header comment
- Added in the code for proper AMD module importing
- Closes #4357

title: Adding definitions for Microsoft Visual Studio Services.
body:
This is type definitions for Microsoft Visual Studio Services. The details of the project can be found in: http://www.visualstudio.com/integrate/extensions/overview

We haven't decided yet how to approach testing since this a combination of multiple definition files which is mostly used for performing a Rest Client call to different services. However, we'll come up with a strategy soon.
